docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — The e-scooter boom began in Santa Monica, Calif., about 16 months ago. Electric scooters, owned by start-ups looking to mimic the success of ride-hailing companies like Uber, appeared around town. The idea was simple: Use a smartphone app to rent a scooter and then leave it at the end of the ride for the next person.

headline.main: In Portland, Scooter Start-Ups Played Nice. Regulators Took Note.
headline.print_headline: The Scooters Came, but They Didn’t Conquer

docs.abstract: Airline cards offer free checked bags and priority boarding. But general-use cards with travel perks are often a better choice, an analysis found.
docs.snippet: Airline cards offer free checked bags and priority boarding. But general-use cards with travel perks are often a better choice, an analysis found.
docs.lead_paragraph: You’ve heard the pitch on your flights: Apply for an airline’s credit card and get perks like waived bag fees, priority boarding and miles for every dollar you spend.

headline.main: Best Credit Card for Travelers? Probably Not One From an Airline
headline.print_headline: Your Airline’s Plastic May Be Letting You Down

docs.abstract: A study by the European Central Bank says tariffs on steel and aluminum have caused only modest economic damage, but have rattled business confidence.
docs.snippet: A study by the European Central Bank says tariffs on steel and aluminum have caused only modest economic damage, but have rattled business confidence.
docs.lead_paragraph: FRANKFURT — President Trump’s trade war was supposed to make Europeans feel so much pain they would beg for mercy at the negotiating table. But it’s not working very well, according to a new study by the European Central Bank.

headline.main: Europe Isn’t Feeling Much Pain From Trump Tariffs, Central Bank Says
headline.print_headline: Europe Feeling Little Sting From Trump Tariffs

docs.abstract: The carmaker said its former chairman, who is awaiting trial on financial misconduct charges, was paid 7.8 million euros from a joint venture with Nissan.
docs.snippet: The carmaker said its former chairman, who is awaiting trial on financial misconduct charges, was paid 7.8 million euros from a joint venture with Nissan.
docs.lead_paragraph: TOKYO — Mitsubishi Motors has joined Nissan in accusing Carlos Ghosn of financial wrongdoing, saying on Friday that he secretly received compensation of 7.8 million euros, or almost $9 million, from a joint venture of the two automakers.

headline.main: Mitsubishi Accuses Carlos Ghosn of Taking a Secret $9 Million Payment

docs.abstract: The Taiwanese company’s intent to build a $10 billion plant with 13,000 jobs was hailed by President Trump. It now sees a shift toward research.
docs.snippet: The Taiwanese company’s intent to build a $10 billion plant with 13,000 jobs was hailed by President Trump. It now sees a shift toward research.
docs.lead_paragraph: It was heralded a year and a half ago as the start of a Midwestern manufacturing renaissance: Foxconn, the Taiwanese electronics behemoth, would build a $10 billion Wisconsin plant to make flat-screen televisions, creating 13,000 jobs. President Trump later called the project “the eighth wonder of the world.”

headline.main: Foxconn Reconsidering Plans for a Wisconsin Factory Heralded by Trump
headline.print_headline: Trump Called a TV Factory Project ‘the 8th Wonder.’ It May Fizzle.
